00:13:04,876 --> 00:13:05,843
<i>connected,</i>

261
00:13:06,121 --> 00:13:08,488
<i>as if we were meant
to meet each other.</i>

262
00:13:08,782 --> 00:13:11,079
<i>Amanda's always been
the one for me.</i>

263
00:13:41,060 --> 00:13:42,876
You still haven't gotten it right.

264
00:13:42,976 --> 00:13:45,456
Coming in every second isn't helping.

265
00:13:56,700 --> 00:13:58,768
Great. Broke a string.

266
00:14:02,712 --> 00:14:05,529
I keep messing up in the same place.
It's like I can't hold

267
00:14:05,629 --> 00:14:08,121
the piece in my head.
That's never happened before.

268
00:14:08,221 --> 00:14:09,814
You'll get it. You always do.

269
00:14:09,914 --> 00:14:12,238
What if I don't?
I need this scholarship.

270
00:14:13,664 --> 00:14:14,422
Done.

271
00:14:15,974 --> 00:14:18,381
It's like I'm carrying this
stress in the back of my neck.

272
00:14:18,481 --> 00:14:19,666
Here, let me.

273
00:14:26,856 --> 00:14:28,027
Feels good.

274
00:14:28,127 --> 00:14:28,930
Good.

275
00:14:31,045 --> 00:14:33,125
It's been one thing
after another lately.

276
00:14:33,225 --> 00:14:35,683
- What do you mean?
- First the headaches,

277
00:14:35,783 --> 00:14:38,802
now this pain in my neck.
Forgetting my music...

278
00:14:38,902 --> 00:14:41,358
- You're just nervous.
- I guess

279
00:14:44,761 --> 00:14:47,041
You know, now that I think
about it, I just...

280
00:14:47,141 --> 00:14:49,449
... haven't felt like myself
since prom.

281
00:14:52,756 --> 00:14:54,743
We know that Latnok
sedated her.

282
00:14:54,843 --> 00:14:57,312
It must have been
a very strong dose.

283
00:14:57,515 --> 00:15:00,997
So strong that she's still having
side effects two weeks later?

284
00:15:01,097 --> 00:15:03,939
- Why is there pain in her neck?
- Stress?

285
00:15:04,039 --> 00:15:07,197
- She's nervous about her concert.
- What if it's more than that?

286
00:15:07,297 --> 00:15:09,243
What if they did
something to her?

287
00:15:09,343 --> 00:15:11,512
Kyle, I think
you're being paranoid.

288
00:15:12,352 --> 00:15:13,604
They kidnapped us!

289
00:15:13,704 --> 00:15:17,399
It was all a sick game. Who knows
what else they're capable of?

290
00:15:17,954 --> 00:15:20,655
Let's say you're right,
they did something.

291
00:15:21,381 --> 00:15:22,361
Now what?

292
00:15:24,678 --> 00:15:27,382
Amanda keeps getting stuck
at the same place in her music.

293
00:15:27,482 --> 00:15:30,971
As if her memory's misfiring.
It could be neurological.

294
00:15:32,124 --> 00:15:35,141
Well, it's not like you can just
scan her brain to find out.

295
00:15:37,865 --> 00:15:40,080
Okay. You could
figure out a way.

296
00:15:40,754 --> 00:15:43,354
This never would have happened
if it weren't for me.

297
00:15:43,454 --> 00:15:45,767
I have to make sure
she's all right.

298
00:15:47,892 --> 00:15:50,170
Anything for
your precious Amanda.

299
00:15:55,158 --> 00:15:56,782
Fancy meeting you here.

300
00:15:56,882 --> 00:15:58,723
What a wonderful coincidence.

301
00:16:04,961 --> 00:16:05,910
For me?

302
00:16:06,546 --> 00:16:10,286
I just like to keep them on hand
in case of accidental run-ins.

303
00:16:11,306 --> 00:16:12,815
That's so nice of you.

304
00:16:13,748 --> 00:16:15,583
Why do you sound so surprised?

305
00:16:16,058 --> 00:16:19,319
No, it's just, people don't
buy me flowers very often.

306
00:16:19,786 --> 00:16:22,480
Well, then you've been dating
the wrong people.

307
00:16:22,648 --> 00:16:25,933
I mean accidentally running into
the wrong people.

308
00:16:27,817 --> 00:16:30,033
We're really doing this,
aren't we?

309
00:16:30,133 --> 00:16:32,093
I'm willing to take the risk.

310
00:16:32,767 --> 00:16:35,346
I mean, that's assuming
that you want to.

311
00:16:36,720 --> 00:16:39,087
I took three buses
just to get here.

312
00:16:39,748 --> 00:16:41,042
Of course I do.

313
00:16:42,569 --> 00:16:45,089
It's just never been
this easy before.

314
00:16:45,559 --> 00:16:48,425
No games, it's so direct. Just...

315
00:16:50,002 --> 00:16:51,009
honesty.

316
00:16:56,915 --> 00:16:59,244
Well... No.
It's not easy.

317
00:16:59,967 --> 00:17:01,525
I mean, we're being bad.

318
00:17:01,625 --> 00:17:04,197
Secretive.
Downright duplicitous.

319
00:17:04,297 --> 00:17:05,554
We are so evil.

320
00:17:07,017 --> 00:17:09,410
Would you care
to be evil over pizza?

321
00:17:10,835 --> 00:17:12,146
I would love to.

322
00:17:21,235 --> 00:17:23,118
Best accidental run-in ever.

323
00:17:33,743 --> 00:17:36,866
- Is that what happened to my Xbox?
- I needed to wire this controller.

324
00:17:36,966 --> 00:17:40,609
- What do I get out of this deal?
- Knowing that you helped Amanda.

325
00:17:40,709 --> 00:17:42,428
That's no reward for me, either.

326
00:17:42,528 --> 00:17:45,642
Do you see her? I need to install this
scanner under the piano.

327
00:17:45,742 --> 00:17:47,664
I don't want her to see us.

328
00:17:47,764 --> 00:17:50,638
Oh, yes, you know,
that would be terrible.

329
00:17:50,738 --> 00:17:52,106
You wanted to help.

330
00:17:52,206 --> 00:17:53,631
I'm here, aren't I?

331
00:17:53,731 --> 00:17:55,948
Amanda's next.
Better fire up that scanner thingy.

332
00:17:56,048 --> 00:17:57,884
Find a place backstage
for the receiver.

333
00:17:57,984 --> 00:18:00,211
- What should I do?
- Make sure we don't get caught.

334
00:18:00,311 --> 00:18:01,090
Right.

335
00:18:03,812 --> 00:18:06,584
Excuse me.
Are you a performer?

336
00:18:07,127 --> 00:18:09,038
Performers only in the stage area.

337
00:18:09,138 --> 00:18:10,820
- But I'm just...
- Who are you?

338
00:18:10,920 --> 00:18:12,983
I'm sorry, but you're not
allowed to be here.

339
00:18:13,083 --> 00:18:14,846
- Please leave.
- Oh, my God!

340
00:18:14,946 --> 00:18:16,702
This is the wrong piece!

341
00:18:17,346 --> 00:18:21,257
This is Tchaikovsky and
I wanted Spandus Strapopovich.

342
00:18:21,837 --> 00:18:23,542
Mother! Where are you?

343
00:18:23,924 --> 00:18:26,025
How could you do this to me?
I hate you!

344
00:18:26,125 --> 00:18:28,090
- Young man...
- Are you in charge here?

345
00:18:28,190 --> 00:18:30,362
- I am.
- This is completely unacceptable.

346
00:18:30,462 --> 00:18:32,244
You need to come with me.

347
00:18:37,906 --> 00:18:39,547
What are you doing here?

348
00:18:41,392 --> 00:18:42,644
Wishing you luck.

349
00:18:43,240 --> 00:18:44,682
It's a closed rehearsal.

350
00:18:44,782 --> 00:18:46,155
And I need to focus.

351
00:18:46,993 --> 00:18:48,454
Okay. Well, then...

352
00:18:48,888 --> 00:18:49,848
good luck.

353
00:19:24,002 --> 00:19:26,748
- The device is working perfectly.
- Great.

354
00:19:30,823 --> 00:19:32,345
We make a good team.

355
00:19:33,083 --> 00:19:34,559
Thanks for helping.

356
00:20:03,653 --> 00:20:06,064
- Leave me alone.
- Amanda, I just want to help.

357
00:20:06,164 --> 00:20:07,820
By showing up with your housemate?

358
00:20:07,920 --> 00:20:10,005
You know how that makes me feel,
especially now.

359
00:20:10,105 --> 00:20:12,451
- I shouldn't have brought her.
- No, you shouldn't have

360
00:20:12,551 --> 00:20:14,966
But somehow,
she's always around, helping.

361
00:20:16,657 --> 00:20:18,275
Let me ask you something.

362
00:20:18,375 --> 00:20:19,126
What?

363
00:20:19,404 --> 00:20:20,449
That night,

364
00:20:20,549 --> 00:20:22,685
after prom,
when you went looking for me...

365
00:20:22,785 --> 00:20:23,488
Yes?

366
00:20:23,886 --> 00:20:25,085
Was Jessi there?

367
00:20:25,377 --> 00:20:28,582
- Why would you think...
- Just answer the question.

368
00:20:29,377 --> 00:20:31,366
Jessi helped me find you, yes.

369
00:20:31,891 --> 00:20:32,768
I knew it.

370
00:20:33,243 --> 00:20:35,441
Look, I know that night
must seem very strange.

371
00:20:35,541 --> 00:20:38,046
Strange? It's this big
giant question mark,

372
00:20:38,146 --> 00:20:40,658
and now that I know she was
there it makes it all even worse.

373
00:20:40,758 --> 00:20:43,264
- Wherever you go, she goes.
- I know it may seem that way...

374
00:20:43,364 --> 00:20:44,812
No, that's how it is!

375
00:20:44,912 --> 00:20:46,857
And honestly, Kyle, I can't take it!

376
00:20:46,957 --> 00:20:49,623
I've got to nail this audition
and I can't be worrying about

377
00:20:49,723 --> 00:20:52,396
what is and what is not going on with
the two of you all the time.

378
00:20:52,496 --> 00:20:54,422
- I just can't!
- There's nothing going on.

379
00:20:54,522 --> 00:20:56,999
Then maybe you could try
not spending every second with her!

380
00:20:57,099 --> 00:20:58,479
See how that goes.

381
00:21:20,907 --> 00:21:23,950
Oh, cool. You got it to read
the data from the rehearsal.

382
00:21:24,050 --> 00:21:26,648
This is all
of Amanda's brain activity.

383
00:21:26,748 --> 00:21:29,258
- Were you up all night?
- Not all night.

384
00:21:29,502 --> 00:21:30,952
Maybe most of it.

385
00:21:31,052 --> 00:21:33,650
You know, you could have
used your computer.

386
00:21:33,750 --> 00:21:35,499
It wouldn't have bothered me.

387
00:21:35,599 --> 00:21:36,804
This one's fine.

388
00:21:39,267 --> 00:21:42,781
Well, call out the numbers.
I'll input them in the program.

389
00:21:42,881 --> 00:21:44,790
I should do this by myself.

390
00:21:45,504 --> 00:21:46,293
Why?

391
00:21:47,199 --> 00:21:48,157
It's just...

392
00:21:50,307 --> 00:21:53,218
maybe you should go see
what everybody else is up to.

393
00:21:53,911 --> 00:21:55,618
It's Amanda, right?

394
00:21:56,456 --> 00:21:57,476
She hates me.

395
00:21:58,212 --> 00:21:59,843
She doesn't hate you.

396
00:21:59,943 --> 00:22:02,199
She just thinks that we spend
too much time together.

397
00:22:02,299 --> 00:22:04,799
- I've only been trying to help.
- I know.

398
00:22:05,100 --> 00:22:08,973
But she doesn't know the real story,
so it looks different to her.

399
00:22:09,839 --> 00:22:13,585
It must be hard, being with someone
when you have to keep so many secrets.

400
00:22:14,598 --> 00:22:15,481
It is.

401
00:22:15,581 --> 00:22:17,719
I wish I could
tell her everything.

402
00:22:18,470 --> 00:22:19,768
Then why don't you?

403
00:22:20,798 --> 00:22:22,866
I think about
how worried she'd be.

404
00:22:22,966 --> 00:22:26,186
Who knows how much more danger
I'd be putting her in.

405
00:22:26,453 --> 00:22:30,513
I feel like she'd be more protected
if she didn't know the whole truth.

406
00:22:32,042 --> 00:22:33,696
I know the whole truth.

407
00:22:34,231 --> 00:22:36,939
Thankfully, you can
take care of yourself.

408
00:22:38,710 --> 00:22:39,919
Yeah, I guess.

409
00:22:42,987 --> 00:22:45,430
Oh, my God.
There's something there.

410
00:22:46,868 --> 00:22:48,166
You were right.

411
00:22:49,846 --> 00:22:52,034
They put something
in her brain.

412
00:22:57,428 --> 00:22:59,377
- What did you do to Amanda?
- What?

413
00:22:59,545 --> 00:23:02,198
- You put something in her head.
- Kyle, you're being really...

414
00:23:02,298 --> 00:23:03,926
Tell me what it is.

415
00:23:05,832 --> 00:23:08,845
Okay. It's something new
we've developed. It's safe.

416
00:23:09,358 --> 00:23:12,278
Instead of typical sedative you
use an nanoscopic neuro-blocker.

417
00:23:12,378 --> 00:23:14,418
Attaches itself to the receptors
on the brain stem.

418
00:23:14,518 --> 00:23:15,753
Why would you do that?

419
00:23:15,853 --> 00:23:18,002
So she wouldn't remember
anything from that night.

420
00:23:18,102 --> 00:23:20,243
- It should have dissolved.
- Well, it hasn't.

421
00:23:20,343 --> 00:23:22,384
She's having side effects
and I need to get it out.

422
00:23:22,484 --> 00:23:24,629
We can't get it out.
But we might be able

423
00:23:24,729 --> 00:23:26,285
- to disintegrate it.
- We?

424
00:23:26,385 --> 00:23:27,979
You mean Latnok?

425
00:23:28,546 --> 00:23:29,741
I'd like to help.

426
00:23:33,339 --> 00:23:36,329
Kyle, don't try anything
on your own. You could hurt her.

427
00:23:36,515 --> 00:23:39,515
- Let me make a phone call.
- You've done enough.

428
00:23:43,389 --> 00:23:46,111
Hilary, where are you
when I need you?

429
00:23:48,781 --> 00:23:50,249
Where are you off to?

430
00:23:52,620 --> 00:23:53,973
Amanda's concert?

431
00:23:56,505 --> 00:23:59,069
Crap. You can totally tell
when I'm lying, huh?

432
00:24:00,071 --> 00:24:01,272
Just like Kyle.

433
00:24:02,504 --> 00:24:04,194
You're going to meet Mark.

434
00:24:05,168 --> 00:24:06,019
Listen...

435
00:24:08,097 --> 00:24:09,943
Let me break it down for you.

436
00:24:11,465 --> 00:24:14,189
When it comes to living in this house,
I know we all gather round

437
00:24:14,289 --> 00:24:16,859
the kitchen island and yuk it up
and we're all smiles and hugs

438
00:24:16,959 --> 00:24:20,199
and touching moments,
but underneath, it is us versus them.

439
00:24:20,560 --> 00:24:22,342
Everyone under legal voting age

440
00:24:22,442 --> 00:24:24,798
is honor-bound to keep each
other's secrets.

441
00:24:25,767 --> 00:24:28,674
- Well, I can keep a secret.
- Great.

442
00:24:31,210 --> 00:24:33,246
- That's it?
- As long as you don't rat me out

443
00:24:33,346 --> 00:24:35,364
- to Mom and Dad, you're in.
- I won't.

444
00:24:35,643 --> 00:24:37,220
- Fine.
- Good.

445
00:24:40,766 --> 00:24:42,839
You know, you should
wear your hair down.

446
00:24:43,448 --> 00:24:45,608
Long healthy hair helps signal
a prospective male

447
00:24:45,776 --> 00:24:47,360
to your reproductive potential.

448
00:24:49,406 --> 00:24:52,240
Okay, thanks.
That's good to know.

449
00:25:05,050 --> 00:25:06,266
How's it going, man?

450
00:25:07,019 --> 00:25:08,980
Good, man. Really good.

451
00:25:09,080 --> 00:25:12,252
I'm close to a breakthrough on
the three dimensional algorithm.

452
00:25:13,041 --> 00:25:14,258
Glad to hear it.

453
00:25:14,629 --> 00:25:15,629
Look.

454
00:25:18,230 --> 00:25:21,815
I heard through the grapevine you've
been spending time with Lori Trager.

455
00:25:25,381 --> 00:25:26,794
I guess.

456
00:25:27,258 --> 00:25:28,943
She's a great girl.

457
00:25:29,629 --> 00:25:30,680
No doubt.

458
00:25:31,670 --> 00:25:32,491
But...

459
00:25:33,774 --> 00:25:35,893
you know how we like
to keep things confidential.

460
00:25:37,630 --> 00:25:38,452
And...

461
00:25:38,620 --> 00:25:41,614
Our goal is to get our guy
back in the fold.

462
00:25:42,129 --> 00:25:44,556
You were never supposed
to make contact with his sister.

463
00:25:45,031 --> 00:25:47,619
I know. We met by accident.

464
00:25:47,719 --> 00:25:50,237
It was just a...
I'll keep things separate.

465
00:25:50,337 --> 00:25:52,184
I mean, we're just hanging out.

466
00:25:52,988 --> 00:25:54,338
Not anymore.

467
00:25:59,393 --> 00:26:02,136
- Jessi, hey!
- Your pants are down.

468
00:26:02,236 --> 00:26:03,898
Oh, look at that.

469
00:26:04,280 --> 00:26:05,672
What are you doing?

470
00:26:05,960 --> 00:26:08,259
I... was just thinking of...

471
00:26:08,576 --> 00:26:10,511
- Hey, she's pretty.
- Don't look at that!

472
00:26:14,062 --> 00:26:15,198
Are you okay?

473
00:26:16,207 --> 00:26:17,241
Knee...

474
00:26:17,516 --> 00:26:18,609
broken.

475
00:26:20,090 --> 00:26:21,083
Leave.

476
00:26:22,059 --> 00:26:22,872
Out!

477
00:26:32,029 --> 00:26:34,341
Good. I need your help
figuring this out.

478
00:26:34,441 --> 00:26:36,640
I thought you couldn't
be seen with me.

479
00:26:36,740 --> 00:26:38,346
I don't have time for that.

480
00:26:38,920 --> 00:26:42,116
What we saw is a neuro-block
which hasn't been dissolved.

481
00:26:42,216 --> 00:26:45,673
It's keeping Amanda's memory of what
to play from getting to her fingers.

482
00:26:45,773 --> 00:26:48,925
But I think I can eliminate it
with an electrical charge.

483
00:26:49,966 --> 00:26:52,234
How do I do it
without electrocuting her?

484
00:26:52,334 --> 00:26:54,528
That's a risk
I'd be willing to take.

485
00:26:56,337 --> 00:26:58,513
I know.
You don't have time for this.

486
00:27:02,095 --> 00:27:03,713
- That's Amanda's head?
- Right.

487
00:27:03,813 --> 00:27:04,919
It's empty.

488
00:27:05,105 --> 00:27:06,899
You don't have to be here.

489
00:27:06,999 --> 00:27:09,506
Except this is my room now.

490
00:27:10,763 --> 00:27:13,258
I have to regulate the voltage
and apply the right amount

491
00:27:13,358 --> 00:27:15,909
to disintegrate the block.
But without hurting her.

492
00:27:25,483 --> 00:27:27,140
- That's not enough.
- I know.

493
00:27:27,240 --> 00:27:29,019
You need more power
if you want it to work.

494
00:27:29,119 --> 00:27:31,168
I know.
Let me concentrate.

495
00:27:38,754 --> 00:27:39,682
That's it.

496
00:27:40,888 --> 00:27:42,053
You're doing it.

497
00:27:43,290 --> 00:27:44,107
More.

498
00:27:45,243 --> 00:27:46,074
More.

499
00:27:48,053 --> 00:27:48,982
More.

500
00:27:50,466 --> 00:27:51,405
More.

501
00:28:02,333 --> 00:28:03,869
I think I need to touch Amanda

502
00:28:03,969 --> 00:28:06,085
to control the electrical flow
more precisely.

503
00:28:06,766 --> 00:28:08,673
She'll feel it and
know what you're doing.

504
00:28:08,773 --> 00:28:10,444
Not if I can distract her.

505
00:28:10,544 --> 00:28:12,248
While you're zapping her?

506
00:28:13,611 --> 00:28:14,962
Does someone want to explain

507
00:28:15,062 --> 00:28:17,251
why my laptop just fried
like my brain on drugs?

508
00:28:17,351 --> 00:28:19,054
I must have caused a power surge.

509
00:28:19,239 --> 00:28:20,837
Sorry. I'll fix it later.

510
00:28:20,937 --> 00:28:24,459
Later not so good for me. I was
in the middle of something important.

511
00:28:24,559 --> 00:28:26,177
Charlotte Cam Live.

512
